The paper deals with the performance analysis of a coding scheme for MIMO communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the effect of block fading channels on the performance of the coding scheme, which is related to the sub-categories of mobile computing and networking (cs.MS), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY).
